  "faq1Question": "How to connect a child device?",
  "faq1Answer": "1. Open the app on your child's device and select \"Child\".\n2. Enter the 6-digit PIN from the Parent Settings page.\n3. Select or create a child profile.\n4. Turn on Child Mode.",
  "faq2Question": "Why can blocked apps still be opened?",
  "faq2Answer": "Please ensure that:\n• Accessibility Service is enabled.\n• Child Mode is turned on.\n• Kid Guard app is running in the background.\n\nIf it still doesn't work, try force stopping Kid Guard and opening it again.",
  "faq3Question": "How to set a time limit?",
  "faq3Answer": "1. Go to Dashboard > Time Limit.\n2. Select a child profile.\n3. Set your desired time limits.\n4. Save changes.\n\nThe child's screen will be locked when the limit is reached.",
  "faq4Question": "How to view child's location?",
  "faq4Answer": "1. Go to Dashboard > Location.\n2. Select a child profile.\n3. The location will be displayed on the map.\n\nNote: Location Permission must be enabled on the child's device.",
  "faq5Question": "What to do if I lost my PIN?",
  "faq5Answer": "1. Go to Settings > Connection.\n2. Tap \"Regenerate\" to create a new PIN.\n3. Use the new PIN to connect.\n\nNote: Already connected devices do not need the new PIN.",
  "faq6Question": "How to delete a child profile?",
  "faq6Answer": "1. Open the app on the child's device.\n2. Select \"Connect with Parent\".\n3. Press and hold the profile you want to delete.\n4. Confirm deletion.",
  "faq7Question": "How does the Rewards system work?",
  "faq7Answer": "You can award points to your child for tasks like homework or chores. They can use these points to redeem custom rewards (e.g., extra game time) from the Rewards section.",
